{
  "texts": [
    "The architecture can therefore produce different outputs for the same input data, each sampled from the corresponding latent distribution.",
    "The encoder and decoder neural networks are trained by gradient descent and backpropagation, enabled by a re-parameterisation of the distribution sampling 48.",
    "The training process for the VAE involves simultaneous training of the encoder and decoder networks with a compound loss function L,",
    "where N t denotes the total number of points the in x.",
    "The first term in the loss function is the reconstruction loss, L rec, which measures the model accuracy in reconstructing the input data from the reduced latent-space representation."
  ]
}